column1: #Text=Penny, 8.A., of Trinity College, Cambridge late exhibitioner of the Kings School, Sherborne, and son of Mr.
#Text=Penny, of this town, has been appointed to a Classical Mastership at Christs Hospital, London.
#Text=Penny took a second class in Classics, Classical Tripos, 1864.
#Text=It is with much regret we have to record the death of Mrs.
#Text=Harston, mother of the vicar, the Rev.
#Text=The venerable lady expired during the time the rev. gentleman was preaching at the Abbey Church on Sunday week.
#Text=The deceased was the daughter of Rear-Admiral Cooke.
#Text=—On Wednesday last the half-yearly audit of G.
#Text=Wingfield Digby, Esq., was held at the Kings Arms Hotel.
#Text=After the dispatch of the formal business, a large number of the tenantry sat down to an excellent dinner in the Town Hall, provided by Mrs.
#Text=Digby, proposed the usual loyal toasts, which were followed by those ot " The Chairman," " Mr.
